	<h1>About gedantic</h1>
	<p>
		gedantic is written using <a href="http://gedcom4j.org">gedcom4j</a>, a java-based library for parsing and writing genealogy data
		in GEDCOM format. It's intended to be both a useful tool in its own right, and to be a demonstration of what gedcom4j can do.
	</p>
	<p>The name is a portmanteau of "gedcom" and "pedantic" - since it's job is to nitpick through your gedcom file and look for
		anomalies and things.</p>
	<p>
		Source is available at <a href="http://github.com/frizbog/gedantic">http://github.com/frizbog/gedantic</a>.
	</p>
